sms._body: Poppy said she was concerned about Jade, as she's very ill. Is she?
No need to answer about Jade. I hope you'll take her to the vet if she is indeed very ill.

I see that you tried to link your saying you won't be paying for the phone or the insurance on the car with me saying that I'd like our divorce to proceed as quickly as possible. Those were two separate parts of the conversation, unrelated to each other. I only mention this for accuracy, as you're clearly structuring your messages as though you expect them to be read by a judge at some point.
I have an appointment at 3:45 today, as a reminder.
Ok, so 3:30?
Sure
I still need my mail
It was in one of the bags I gave you yesterday
Scottie left a black suitcase in the gear room. He needs to get it.
If you can bring it to me, I can get it to him.
Sure
What time do you want to meet to pick up Holland today?
Good morning, Holland is growing out of all his socks! Also, I need some of his toys here. The developmental stuff, preferably.
On the road, we'll be at the spot at 7
On target?
Yup
Did you order the seat for Holland?
Poppy is saying her vagina is really hurting her. Any ideas? My initial thought was her new bike seat but she said she didn't ride her bike that much.

She did say her bottom hurt riding her bike but she never said anything about her vagina. Can't think of anything else it could be... She did think she had to pee earlier but didn't, could that be a UTI?
Oh no....

It sure could be. She's especially vulnerable now that she's using the toilet in her own. I always insist on  cleaning her with a wipe after she poops. We should probably really be stressing the front-to-back method.
Yeah, I really hope that's not it. Good call on the wipes with a poop, I'll start doing that too
Cool

And lots and lots of water. I try to offer her water at least once an hour. If she asks for anything, (food/drink) I tell her to drink a glass of water first. She's good about it. Constant flushing is a good back up.
For sure
I am so terribly sick. I can barely swallow, everything aches, deep whole body chills.

Oh no! If you need me to take the kids so you can sleep, I may be able to arrange something. I still don't know all the specifics of my schedule this week, but should have a better sense be end if day.
That would be a dream. I'm in a complete haze. Dizzy, "wah-wah-wah" sound in my ears, my throat is so swollen I can barely get water down.
I hope your first day is going well.
Ok, let's touch base tonight.
What time do you you get off?

Asking me to not factor-in your domestic violence is Completely unreasonable. The fact that you hit me is the reason our family is torn apart. Your lack of self-restraint is everything here. Asking me to set that aside comma when dealing with our children and their futures, is unreasonable. That would make me a terrible mother.

Additionally, when you say that you're open to negotiation, and then shut it down completely because you're not getting exactly what you want, especially when it's a matter of one day difference, it leads me to believe that the situation you're asking for has little to do the actual time you'll be spending with the kids and everything to do with some other Factor.

You asked me the day before yesterday if I could understand why you're angry with me for calling the police. The truthful answer to that is no. Absolutely not. You should be angry with yourself. You should feel shame for losing control and hitting your wife, in front of your child. You should be so disappointed in yourself and apologetic for your behavior. That is the way a mentally healthy person would respond to what is transpired. The fact that you went into overdrive immediately and started building a case for yourself, and saying and doing everything in your power to not take any responsibility for what you've done makes me believe, finally, that you actually do need all of the classes and counseling that folks have been suggesting to me that you need.
We have a big issue here.
Where did all of the paperwork from the middle drawer of the desk go? I had many things in there.
I'd like to know where that is while I'm here. I need to retrieve things.
It's in that corner of the garage in a box
I gave Jade food and water for you.
Cool
Do you have Poppy's SSN handy?
Nope
It seems my tools, but I entered into the relationship with, are in Olympia still. May I borrow a hammer from you?
Sure, but I'll need it back ASAP cuz I use it alot.
Looks like you have two or three down there. I'm upstairs nursing Hall and right now so I'm not certain. Have a preference on which one I take?
I have two, you can take either, but you may want the small one cuz the big one has a waffle head that can damage finished surfaces
Poppy wants some of the snacks you have here. I kind of don't feel comfortable just giving her your food. Cool with you? She wants crackers, peanut butter and she saw the trail mix.
Thanks for asking, she can eat anything she wants, and you can too, please don't take the whole bag/box of anything though.
Those wasabi almonds are pretty dang good
She helped herself to the almond butter before I got a response from you. I'd like to take my orchids.
Cool, that's fine
I totally forgot the platters!
Oh, and Holland had an enormous blow out while we were there. I used some your wipes and a diaper. I tossed his clothes in the laundry basket in poppies closet and borrowed a firetruck suit
Cool
Have you thought about the schedule next week, because I have the kids this weekend?
Maybe I can have them Monday and Tuesday night? Pick up after work Monday.
I'll take them while you work?
Which sounds great to me.
I was planning on having mom come up. It's not convenient to meet up in Roosevelt before work
I'm not going to be away from Holland 2 nights in a row.
I mean full days and night
So, I get what you're saying about an additional stop in the morning. Meeting Monday evening is fine. I will want Holland on Tuesday during the day. Let me know if you have any ideas.
Also, poppy wanted me to mention that she would like to have a ladies night with me this week.
Holland has a pediatrician appointment next week. Has he been added to the insurance for certain? Also, if so, does he have a number or a
He's still covered under united with discovery, that's good until the end of the month.
Do we have a card for him?
Also, can we trade cars tomorrow?
I need to fit the 4 of us, plus 20 balloons, cake, all the food, etc.
Sorry can't, I need the Tahoe tomorrow.
Biking? For the rack?
What time are you leaving tomorrow? I need to pick up the platters and a tablecloth
And I should probably pick up that I insurance card from you before next week too.
I'm not sure exactly, probably around ten.
Okay, mind if I give you a short list of things in the morning, leaving them at the door?
What time do you need to come by?
And yes that's fine
8 ish

One of the oval platters That match my dishes, (I'm also missing a plate, if you know where that is), the blue rectangular plate, 2 round dishes (cabinet the Mason jars were kept in, top shelf-to put utensils in upright), my knife cutting set (drawer where the aluminum foil was kept-in grey velvet box)
She's upset
Please tell her I'm not here
You break a no contact order all the time. Don't be a dick to your daughter.
I'm upset too
No I don't
Seriously, dude she's expecting you to say happy birthday to her. I could walk into the garage but you've disabled my garage door opener.
You also have already had phone conversations with her, on my phone,. You could have answered your call. Again, you're showing your true colors.
She knows you can talk to her on the phone.
It's easy for you to be cavalier about the order where you sit, but not me
You should never set up expectations for her that involve violation of the order as it's written. That's cruel to both of us.

I'm not being Cavalier about it. You know that you're allowed to speak to her on the phone. She knows that you're allowed to speak to her on the phone. You've already done it. You pick and choose when you want to adhere to the no contact order
I didn't set up any expectations but I'm not being cruel. Don't be ridiculous.
And

You can spend this any way you want to but we both now, and if you haven't confirmed with your attorney that's your oversight not mine, that you can speak with your daughter on the phone. You're making a choice now not too. Yet another situation where I get to see who you truly are.

To be clear, when we drive up the driveway, I told Poppy we wouldn't see you. She said, "Of course we will, Mommy! He's going to tell me happy birthday party day." Otherwise, I wouldn't have even considered it.
Are you planning to see the kids tomorrow?
Yeah, so I talked to my mom and she can drop off and pick up Holland on Tuesday.
I hope you guys are having a nice Easter, please say happy Easter to your mom and poppy for me.
Sounds good. I'm arranging to get my mom back to the airport tomorrow so what time do you want to meet to exchange the kids tomorrow?
I can do it at like 6, after work.
That's fine.
If your mom would like to weekend some time with Holland on Tues, I can meet her at noon.
If you'd like to see him more than the one night, I can bring him back Tues evening.
Yeah, I'd definitely like to have him Tuesday night as well.
Your mom will be there both nights?
Yeah
Meet at 6?
To pick up Holland? I figured mom would do that...
Why would your mom do that?
Because she has the Tahoe and thus the car seats. Did she meet you this morning?
I'm still waiting for her to confirm for me that she can leave now to meet me.
The car seat issue makes sense. I'll arrange the childcare with your mother.
Cool, thanks
There is an event next Saturday for some of the girls from Cheetah's class and the moms. I'd like to take her. It's from 2:30-4.
Cool
I need SSNs for you and the kids to enroll health insurance. FYI, I will have to remove you apparently after divorced, but I can still add for now if you'd like.
nursing now. I'll get the kid's when I'm finished
Cool, sounds good
Have you looked at the summer preschool camp info yet? We really need to get her registered. before it fills up.
I looked a little, but I can look closer later this week.
They're filling up. You're home now?
Yeah, just got back
Okay. I'm waiting for your mom.
Have you seen my old blue bike helmet?
Maybe you can take a look at that info now.
Nope
K
Was that a new bike you had on the Tahoe Sat?
No, it's my really old one. I've been biking to the University of Washington Light Rail with that bike.
So please put it on your calendar that you won't be able to go to Olympia next weekend, as I am taking poppy to that event Saturday afternoon.
Nice!
It didn't seem mountain bikey.
Yeah, it's in there :-) well likely ski that morning with Matt and Callum.
Don't know these people
If you could look at that preschool Camp stuff now, that would be helpful. I'd really like to get her signed up tonight, if possible.
Your mom just got here to take care of the kids for you.
Looking at camps. I think we should do the weeks a month of the preschool camps split between the montlake and laurelhurst centers. All those look really cool. Science explorers and such.

I'm looking at the one in Madison Park. It's available every week. It's a two-minute walk from my house. It happens at the beach house / bathhouse right there by the park. This way she will meet all the kids in the neighborhood.
I can't believe you just took poppy like that. I thought we had an understanding that I would have the kids for two nights as usual.

We didn't discuss it. I had no idea you thought that you were having her tonight. We only discussed Holland. I get where you're coming from, because we didn't discuss it, and I understand the timing. But, no, I had no thought that she would be spending the night with you, considering she has school in the morning.
I didn't mean to cause an issue.
Did you file taxes joint or separately?

Even when you're angry, life continues. We still need to discuss things. 
1. Did you file jointly or separately?
2. I need to get Poppy registered for her summer camp before it fills up.
I still need those SSNs.
Filed jointly
And I'd like to split the camp time between Madison beach and laurelhurst center, as I'd also like her to meet kids who live up this way.

You do not have the kids during the week and it does not make sense for me to drive poppy in and out of another neighborhood, and create a commute for myself, unnecessarily. I also, more over, don't want her to get into a group and then be pulled out of it and have to make a whole batch of new friends.
Pulled out? Not sure what your talking about there... And I plan do have them during the week a decent amount as it is, and intend to have them more now that I have the new job.

So, you have expressed since before we had children, that you believe that not going into daycare is the best thing for them. You've expressed, to many many people, that you are very pleased that Poppy has had a parent available to her during the day. So, what about this has changed? How has something you seemed to believe so strongly changed so drastically? So you now believe that children should be in daycare four days a week?

By pulled out, I meant, that she would be spending a few weeks getting to know a group of friends and neighbors in one spot. Then you believe that she should leave that group and enter into an entirely different program, in an entirely different neighborhood, and have to make all new friends? You realize, friends will have been established by this point. She'll be the new kid. It will not be as easy as it was with everyone entering in new on the same day.

I have no idea what makes you say that. Daycare is one of many child care options and the least desirable. When I have them, my mom is able to take them during work. And you are going to have to work now too, so the landscape has changed. This is the type of conversation I'd like to have whey a mediator as text is not an ideal medium. I Have to get ready for work now.

You have no idea why I would say that you have always said that you are thrilled that the kids don't have to go into daycare? You have no idea why you I would say that you have told many many people how happy you are that you have a parent who was willing to stay home with our kids? You have no idea why I would say that?
So, you intend to have your mother raise our children. Interesting.

Also interesting, is when I told you that I would like to go back to work after Holland was born, you said that we could discuss this when Holland was in school. So, you have no real plan for our children. You're just making this up as you go along, depending on what's convenient for you, or what will be hurtful to me. Got it.

Luckily, I have integrity and every intention of sticking to the plan that we decided, together, would be the best route for our children. Whether it's convenient for me or not. Even when I'm hurt and angry, I get up and get my job done. Without asking my mother to do it for me.
I need those SSNs so I can get the kids insured.
I'm driving poppy to school right now. I have an appointment after that. I'll get them for you when I get back to the house today.

I'm headed to the house right now to pick up Holland. I'm letting you know, as a courtesy, that I plan to go inside and get some socks for poppy. She only has the tall socks at our house that she was with boots. All of her shorts socks are nowhere to be found.

So if you go to Seattle.gov/parks, enter the bar code, then hit the "add" button, are you able to log in?
I've looked all over my place and all through the car. I don't have Holland's Social Security card.
Ok I'll call the SS office today and see if I can get it that way. Dates for camp?
Running errands
K, whenever your back, just send it and we'll get this locked down.
Just headed back now. 6 tonight?
Yeah, sounds good
And the schedule for tomorrow?
I'll drop off poppy when you need me to, then I'd love to have the kids for the rest of the weekend.
I'll meet you at 2. Then I'll let you know when we're finished with the event. I want a chunk of time to nurse him.
Do you plan to stay in Seattle this weekend?
Yeah, so will you take both of them at 2 tomorrow?
Yes, that makes the most sense.
Ok, that's fine with me. Any idea about how long?

I just spoke with social security and the only eaway they'll give us his number is if we go into a local office and present a passport or driver's license for one of us and an original of his birth certificate as well as another document such as an immunization record for him. I can do that on Monday but would need to get those docs from you. Do you have an original medical document of that sort?
Awesome!!!!!
(Enormous) Inconvenience averted!
Yes indeed :-)
Will you please feed Holland right before we meet up?
Sure
Can you give me the camp schedule you'd like for poppy?
Just start at the week of 7/3 and continue for the weeks you're willing to pay for. I think continuous is best for her, socially. I'll work everything else around that.
Ok

Yup

Awesome
Did Holland just have a bottle?
Let's meet at 6, take some extra time

No, don't need any more time. We'll see you in a bit.
Cool, it was a very nice thought :-)
Sorry I didn't mention it sooner.
All good, I got a nice little ride in so I appreciate the time I did get.
The carrier! Flipping around
Cool

Ok, woke up a lot in the first half, better from 2am on.

You were going to start depositing 4k this month.

I said I thought that the new job would allow me to go up to that. I didn't specify a time or guarantee it. I just had to pay that 600 phone bill and a surprise insurance Co pay from last June (for an unscheduled ultrasound) of 1300. So things are very tight because of that. I need to see exactly how much my checks are and how much the insurance employee contributions are so I can finalize my budget. I'm sorry for any confusion and assure you I'm doing everything I can.

Yes, you said specifically the second half of April you would start depositing 4000. Very specifically. It's just another experience of you breaking your word.  You did get a large signing bonus. Thousands of dollars. You can easily take the 500 out of that. How many tens of thousands of dollars was that, by the way? Also, the unscheduled ultrasound you're referring to is the emergency room visit while I was pregnant, and in terrible pain, with our child. Remember that day? So not a surprise at all. That was the day that you promised if I still went with you to the wedding in Canada that you would do all the child care. And then that night when you told me you were going to go drink with all the guys, and I reminded you that I wasn't supposed to lift poppy in and out of her crib, you called me a f****** c***. That night.
Yeah, go ahead and just take that 500 out of the tens of thousands you got for your signing bonus.

You also told me that you're doubling up on work for the end of April. So, you're getting paid from two different companies. You make a lot of money. You can afford the $4,000 a month to go to supporting your children.

Moving into a home, that isn't a two-story three bedroom, two thousand square foot home for a single man for over $3,000, will make it much easier for you to be able to keep the commitments that you make to your children. Again, a shift in your priorities is going to be necessary for this to work successfully.

Um isn't that simple, you still have a ton of stuff here the logistics of moving out or a bit more than I can handle right now and then there's the dog issue as well. I'm still thinking of moving out but can't do it immediately. I'm not sitting on tons of money my entire bonus is gone to that $8,000 credit card bill these surprise expenses and having to pay Lucy and Christians entire security and pet deposit out of pocket because it was all spent. I also didn't expect to be paying your car insurance and cell phone at this point I would have figured you would made arrangements for those expenses on your own. I'm hoping to get closer to what a realistic alimony situation would be so that I can have a budget that I can plan around. I'm sorry you're upset about this, and I still think I can get up to what I was hoping to get up to monthly for you. But there are a lot of circumstances that make now really difficult and I have no money, it's as simple as that.
You have no money? You mean your accounts are empty?
And you were able to pay off all your credit cards cards? while I'm still carrying a balance from those expenses from November and December?

You know, this is futile. I don't actually expect you to do anything according to what's right, or from the goodness of your heart. I know that you live to Serve Yourself. Above and beyond anything else in your life. I was just another employee to you. I get that. It's just amazing to finally be able to express myself freely without having to fear what's going to happen afterward.

You like to talk about how generous you are, and how well you take care of your family, but that's not the reality. You only do things when there's someone to see that you're doing good things. Behind the scenes, it's all about angling for the best opportunity for yourself.

You have all week, with no parental responsibilities, and help on the weekends. You can easily look for a new place for yourself. You had months to do this. You worked from home and set your own schedule. You were able to go out for breakfast with friends and get away in the evenings. Your priorities have been misaligned for a long long time.

I'm not saying no. I'm telling you she hasn't mentioned it today while I'm. nursing Holland, helping her get Jammies on, and trying to get her down for a nap

It feels obvious that you're trying to hurt me financially. You've threatened my credit already. Now you believe that your credit cards should all be paid off and mine should be hanging out there growing? You with the job and me with the kids? At what point did I not do my job?
I'm really sorry for the confusion but I never guaranteed a time I could increase. I'm also unsure what family expenses you're referring to.
All of our bills, food, Christmas presents, every single thing we purchased in November and December.

All the charges, on my card.

I'm talking about charges from NOVEMBER AND DECEMBER. She started in Jan. The other ladies, we paid with my card, and one with a check.

See them/

She just told me you did.
She's 4

6pm as usual tonight?

Thanks. The thing that I don't think the mechanics perspective acknowledges is the high cost of repairs on any Mercedes. And our entire conversation was regarding the cost of parts and labor for the Mercedes.
Maybe he's never owned an 1800$ Camry?
Yeah totally
His entire business is cars. He owns the shop. What he says makes sense to me.

But, yeah, we should just trade cars. We can sell the Mercedes. I'll drive the kids in the Tahoe, because it's the safe or car. After all, we got it so that Holland would be up higher while he was young.
You fit all your ski gear, and a bike rack on a Camry for years. I don't know why I was thinking you couldn't do that now :-)
